titleInfo.subTitle: FINDINGS and RECOMMENDATIONS signed by Magistrate Judge Craig M. Kellison on 1/5/15 Recommending that Defendants' MOTION 10 to DISMISS be granted. Plaintiff's complaint be dismissed with leave to file an amended complaint consistent with the above discussion. The claims against defendant California Highway Patrol under 42 U.S.C. ยง 1983 be dismissed without leave to amend. Plaintiff may file an amended complaint within 30 days of the date of this order. These Findings and Recommendations are submitted to the U.S District Judge Morrison C. England, Jr. Objections to these Findings and Recommendations due Within 20 days. (Mena-Sanchez, L)

titleInfo.title: (PS)O'Keefe v. California Highway Patrol et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Chief Judge Morrison C. England, Jr. on 2/12/2015 ORDERING that the 12 Findings and Recommendations are ADOPTED IN FULL. This defendants' 10 motion to dismiss is GRANTED, with leave to file an amended complaint against Officer Somovia. The claims against defendant California Highway Patrol under 42 U.S.C. ยง 1983 are DISMISSED without leave to amend. Plaintiff shall file an amended complaint within 30 days of the date of this order. Failure to file an amended complaint within the time provided may be grounds for dismissal of this action in its entirety. (Zignago, K.)
